import numpy as np
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import math

fig = plt.figure()
ax = plt.subplot(111)

xL=np.array([.104, .077, .073, .063, .052, .038, .020, .118, .107, .096])
yL=np.array([7.47, 7.59, 7.61, 7.67, 7.73, 7.76, 7.78, 7.35, 7.36, 7.38])

xU=np.array([.118, .096, .079, .071, .058, .034, .113, .085, .068, .018])
yU=np.array([9.10, 8.88, 8.72, 8.68, 8.45, 8.36, 9.07, 8.78, 8.60,8.12 ])

ax.scatter(xL, yL, c="red", alpha=0.1, label="lower bound measurements")
ax.scatter(xU, yU, c="green", alpha=.1, label="upper bound measurements")
plt.title('Driving Frequency vs. Total Range of Driving Oscillation')
plt.xlabel('Total Range of Driving Oscillation (m)')
plt.ylabel('Driving Frequency (Hz)')

x = np.linspace(0, .12, 1000)
ax.plot(x, -7.09*(x)+8.22, color="red", label="lower bound prediction");
ax.plot(x, +7.09*(x)+8.22, color="green", label="upper bound prediction")

ax.errorbar(xL, yL, yerr=.03, color="red", fmt='.')
ax.errorbar(xU, yU, yerr=.03, color="green", fmt='.')

ax.legend(loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(1.45, 0.8), shadow=True, ncol=1)


plt.show()

fig = plt.figure()
ax = plt.subplot(111)

xL=np.array([.104, .077, .073, .063, .052, .038, .020, .118, .107, .096])
yL=np.array([7.47, 7.59, 7.61, 7.67, 7.73, 7.76, 7.78, 7.35, 7.36, 7.38])

xU=np.array([.118, .096, .079, .071, .058, .034, .113, .085, .068, .018])
yU=np.array([9.10, 8.88, 8.72, 8.68, 8.45, 8.36, 9.07, 8.78, 8.60,8.12 ])

ax.scatter(xL, yL, c="red", alpha=0.1, label="lower bound measurements")
ax.scatter(xU, yU, c="green", alpha=.1, label="upper bound measurements")
plt.title('Driving Frequency vs. Total Range of Driving Oscillation Incorporating Damping')
plt.xlabel('Total Range of Driving Oscillation (m)')
plt.ylabel('Driving Frequency (Hz)')

x = np.linspace(0, .12, 1000)

ax.plot(x, -np.sqrt((7.09*x)**2-5.76*10**-4)+8.22, color="red", label="lower bound with damping prediction");
ax.plot(x, np.sqrt((7.09*x)**2-5.76*10**-4)+8.22, color="green", label="upper bound damping prediction")

ax.errorbar(xL, yL, yerr=.03, color="red", fmt='.')
ax.errorbar(xU, yU, yerr=.03, color="green", fmt='.')

ax.legend(loc='upper center', bbox_to_anchor=(1.45, 0.8), shadow=True, ncol=1)


plt.show()

fig = plt.figure()

xL=np.array([.104, .077, .073, .063, .052, .038, .020, .118, .107, .096])
yL=np.array([7.47, 7.59, 7.61, 7.67, 7.73, 7.76, 7.78, 7.35, 7.36, 7.38])

xU=np.array([.118, .096, .079, .071, .058, .034, .113, .085, .068, .018])

plt.title('Driving Frequency vs. Total Range of Driving Oscillation with Higher Order Terms')
plt.xlabel('Total Range of Driving Oscillation (m)')

x = np.linspace(0, .12, 1000)

ax.plot(x, -1.53*x**2-7.09*(x)+8.22, color="red", label="lower bound with quadratic order");

ax.errorbar(xL, yL, yerr=.03, color="red", fmt='.')
ax.errorbar(xU, yU, yerr=.03, color="green", fmt='.')
